## Admin Portal

The admin portal is completely isolated from the user-facing application.

| URL | Description |
|---|---|
| `/admin-portal/login` | Admin-only login (email + password, no Firebase) |
| `/admin-portal` | Stats overview + quick action shortcuts |
| `/admin-portal/challenges` | Create, edit, delete challenges; toggle premium flag |
| `/admin-portal/submissions` | Filter by status; trigger AI; review + publish/reject |
| `/admin-portal/users` | View all users; manually grant/revoke subscription plans |
| `/admin-portal/email` | Compose and send HTML email blasts to filtered user segments |

### Admin Submission Lifecycle

```
pending
  тЖТ [Admin clicks "Run AI Eval"] тЖТ ai_evaluated
  тЖТ [Admin reviews + saves note]  тЖТ admin_reviewed
  тЖТ [Admin clicks "Publish"]      тЖТ published  (ranks recomputed)
  тЖТ [Admin clicks "Reject"]       тЖТ rejected
```

Only `published` submissions appear on leaderboards and user profiles.

---

## Subscription Plans

| Plan | Price | Duration | Premium Challenges | Team Chat | Team Size |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Free | тВ╣0 | Unlimited | тЭМ | тЭМ | Solo only |
| 10-Day Sprint | тВ╣99 | 10 days | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | Up to 3 |
| Monthly Pro | тВ╣199 | 30 days | тЬЕ | тЬЕ | Unlimited |

Plans are stored per-user with an `expiresAt` date. Expired plans are checked at runtime тАФ no cron job needed. Admins can also manually grant or revoke plans from the Users panel.

> Payment gateway integration point is in `backend/routes/plans.js` тАФ the `POST /api/plans/upgrade` endpoint is ready for Razorpay or Stripe.

---

## Team Collaboration & Chat

Premium users can invite partners to their project submission:

1. **Add team members** by username when submitting
2. All team members can view the submission detail page
3. **Real-time text chat** is available to all team members via Socket.io
4. Chat is scoped to a single submission тАФ each submission has its own room
5. Message history is stored in MongoDB (last 200 messages returned on load)

Non-premium users see the chat section but receive an upgrade prompt.

---

## Leaderboard System

InceptaX has two leaderboard types:

### Global Leaderboard `/leaderboard`
- Aggregates all users who have at least one published submission
- Ranked by each user's **best single project score**
- Shows: rank, name, best score, total submissions, average AI score
- Top 3 displayed in a gold/silver/bronze podium

### Per-Project Leaderboard `/leaderboard/challenge/:id`
- Scoped to a single challenge
- Shows every published submission for that challenge
- Highlights the logged-in user's own rank
- Ranks recomputed automatically every time admin publishes a new result for that challenge

---

## Email System (Nodemailer)

All platform emails are sent via Nodemailer using SMTP (tested with Gmail App Password).

### Automated Emails

| Trigger | Template | Type |
|---|---|---|
| New user signs up (Firebase sync) | Branded welcome with CTA | `welcome` |
| OTP verification request | Large 6-digit code display | `custom` |
| User upgrades a plan | Activation confirmation | `plan_upgrade` |

### Admin Email Blast

Admins can compose and send HTML emails to:
- All users
- Free plan users only
- 10-Day Sprint users only
- Monthly Pro users only

The blast fires asynchronously (100ms delay between sends to avoid rate limits). Every sent email is recorded in `EmailLog` with status, recipient, subject, and body.

### Email Templates

All templates use a consistent dark-themed HTML design matching the platform aesthetic. No external template engine тАФ pure HTML strings with inline styles for maximum email client compatibility.

